In astrophysical environments, it is well known that dust and ice NPs efficiently scatter X-rays due to their grain geometric sizes being on the same scale as the photon wavelengths31,32. In such studies, the classical Mie model is used as an approximation in determining differential and total scattering cross sections for nano-sized particles32. Mie-scattering results when electromagnetic radiation (EMR) interacts with particles with dimensions larger than the EMR wavelength. Due to the sub-nanometre wavelength of X-rays, NPs are extremely efficient Mie scatters of X-rays where the ratio of scattered X-ray intensity Isλ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
